## Patch A: add Docling timeout cleanup visibility test scaffold

Add under `Describe "DoclingAdapter (Mocked / Availability)"`:

```powershell
    Context "Priority 0 cleanup / timeout visibility" {
        It "Keeps extraction failure non-fatal when timeout cleanup path is hit" {
            # Intentionally scoped as a non-invasive behavioral test.
            # The goal is to ensure the adapter still returns a failure record
            # instead of throwing out of the function when timeout handling runs.

            $tmp = Join-Path $TestDrive 'timeout-test.pdf'
            'fake pdf content' | Set-Content -LiteralPath $tmp

            $adapter = New-DoclingAdapter -PythonPath 'C:\NonExistent\python.exe' -TimeoutSeconds 1
            $result = Invoke-DoclingExtraction -FilePath $tmp -Adapter $adapter

            $result | Should -Not -BeNullOrEmpty
            $result.success | Should -Be $false
        }
    }
```

Why this belongs:
- it verifies the function remains graceful on the failure path
- it protects against future refactors that accidentally convert these branches into hard throws

